com.ibm.team.process.common
Interface IIterationType

All Superinterfaces:
IAuditable, IAuditableHandle, IItem, IItemHandle, IIterationTypeHandle, IManagedItem, IManagedItemHandle, INamed, IProcessItem, IProcessItemHandle
public interface IIterationType
extends IIterationTypeHandle, IProcessItem

A type of iteration. Iterations can be assigned to an iteration type and users can then configuration all iterations of a given type at once by configuring the iteration type.

Since:
0.6

Method Detail

getId

java.lang.String getId()
Returns the id of this iteration type or null if no id has been set.

In order for this item to be saved to the repository this field must have a non-null value, so it is safe to assume that this method will not return null if it is an immutable copy fetched from the repository. It is possible for an incomplete/invalid working copy, however, to return null.

Returns:
the id of this iteration type or null

setId

void setId(java.lang.String id)
Sets the id of this iteration type. The provided identifier may not be null.

Parameters:
identifier - the new identifier, may not be null

getLabel

java.lang.String getLabel()
This convenience method returns the name of this iteration type if the name is not null and is not a whitespace string. Otherwise it returns this iteration type's id, which may be null if this item is a working copy (@see getId().

Returns:
the name or id of this iteration or null

isArchived

boolean isArchived()
Returns whether or not this iteration type is archived.

In order to archive an iteration type, use the process client library or process server service.

Returns:
whether or not this iteration type is archived

getProjectArea

IProjectAreaHandle getProjectArea()
Returns the project area which contains this iteration type or null if no project area has been set.

In order for this item to be saved to the repository this field must have a non-null value, so it is safe to assume that this method will not return null if it is an immutable copy fetched from the repository. It is possible for an incomplete/invalid working copy, however, to return null.

Returns:
the project area which contains this iteration type

setProjectArea

void setProjectArea(IProjectAreaHandle projectArea)
Sets this iteration type's project area. In order to complete the bi-directional relationship, callers must also add this iteration type to the project area.

Parameters:
projectArea - the handle of the project area
